    Allura leans back on one elbow, her gaze drifting to the lanterns above, watching them swing faintly with the wind outside.

    <<speech "allura">>My mother, a little. My father... well, I know more about him than I'd like to.<</speech>>

    She runs a finger along the edge of a cushion, as if tracing the outline of a thought she hasn't quite dared to speak aloud.

    <<speech "allura">>My mother was human. Village-born. Hard-edged. She worked with herbs—mostly tinctures and poultices, but also... other things. People came to her with needs they couldn't name. Secrets steeped in boiling water.<</speech>>

    A faint chuckle escapes her lips, but there's no joy in it.

    <<speech "allura">>She never spoke of my father. Not once. I asked often. I didn't understand what I was—so how could I know what he was?<</speech>>

